column1: #FORMAT=WebAnno TSV 3.2
#T_SP=webanno.custom.Referent|entity|infstat
#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=Just random people who have certain things happen in their life .
#Text=Like what ?
#Text=Anything really .
#Text=Like a trauma from school or problems with a family member .
#Text=Things like that .
#Text=How would you treat that person differently than someone who is coming here for the pleasure or the thrill of it ?
#Text=I would be more aware and pay more attention to where the session is taking them .
#Text=You really need to be fully aware of everything that is going on .
#Text=What would be a point where you did n’t feel comfortable with the session ?
#Text=His reaction , if I see he is starting to fall deeper and deeper into depression , whereas sometimes that has happened in sessions .
#Text=Sometimes a guy will cry during the session , or sob uncontrollably .
#Text=Sometimes he will get angry and start screaming .
#Text=In both of those situations , how would you handle it ?
#Text=You start to console them .
#Text=That ’s when you know you are no longer in that session , that It is no longer a role play .
#Text=That is where the psychological really comes into it , when the psychology helps , to be there and to listen .
#Text=Sometimes they are like , “ I killed my pet dog by accident and I ’ve kept this inside for me for so long ! ”
#Text=Or , “ I had a close family member just pass away and I do n’t know how to deal with that right now . ”
#Text=“ My girlfriend just left me —
#Text=“ I mean , you hear all these stories !
#Text=One after the other after the other , and it ’s just like , “ Wow ! ”
#Text=If one is crying , you console them ; if one is angry you try to calm them down .
#Text=Do you give them absolution ?
#Text=Yeah , “ It was n’t your fault what happened .
#Text=You were five years old , how would you know what this would do to the dog , you know ? ”
#Text=A lot of cases you have to help them out with it and at the end of the session they just feel so much better about themselves .
#Text=What do you do when someone gets angry ?
#Text=Usually just try to bring them down and find out about what it is that gets them so angry .
#Text=A lot of times they are not going to come out and say , “ This is what is bothering me . ”

#Text=They are going to veil it so much that you are trying to knock down so many walls they put up , and finally it can be one word , one comment , a simple thing that you might say that might trigger something , and then you realize what happened .
#Text=A lot of times you try to keep it within the role play , as well , which is what really makes the session great , but you just calm them down .
